  "markdown": "[Skip to main content](https://dragselect.com/docs/guided-examples/Mobile-Touch#__docusaurus_skipToContent_fallback)\n\n# Mobile/Touch usage\n\n**Congratulations, DragSelect can be used on a mobile by default ðŸŽ‰**\n\nKeep in mind that using DragSelect on a mobile/touch device will also turn off the default scroll behavior (on `click` \\+ `drag` interaction).\n\nIn 99% of the use-cases, this is what you want.\n\nHowever, if DragSelect is only one part of a website, and you still want to be able to scroll the page on mobile, you can use an `area` [see settings](https://dragselect.com/docs/API/Settings). This way the default scroll behavior remains intact for the rest of the page.\n\nFor example like this:\n\n```codeBlockLines_AclH\nconst ds = new DragSelect({\n  selectables: document.querySelectorAll('.selectable'),\n  area: document.querySelector('#area'),\n});\n\n```",
